## Context

- Phase 1a (#1005) done: SWI/SNF classifier — 157 ARID1A-mut, 72 SMARCA4-mut, 16 dual, 1874 WT across 2119 lines.
- Phase 1b (#1006) done: Metabolic dependency screen — 1590 KEGG metabolic genes screened. SMARCA4-ovarian has strong OXPHOS signal.
- Phase 2 (#1007) done: Cross-atlas validation — 104 convergent metabolic genes (SL in both ARID1A & SMARCA4). 34 are OXPHOS/ETC genes. HMGCR does NOT cross-validate (ARID1A-specific). SMARCA4 mito genes (MICOS13, HIGD2A, COX6C) DO cross-validate to ARID1A.
- Phase 3 (#1008) done: Pathway enrichment — OXPHOS is dominant (4.3x enriched, FDR=2.56e-13). Lipoic acid also enriched (5.6x, FDR=4.45e-03). Ranked analysis confirms SMARCA4 OXPHOS shift (median d=-0.905).
- Key finding: SWI/SNF metabolic convergence is OXPHOS-driven, not cholesterol. All 5 ETC complexes vulnerable in both ARID1A and SMARCA4 mutants.
- Tasks remaining: #1009 (Phase 4 TCGA expression, p3), #1010 (Phase 5 drug repurposing, p3)
- Next priority: Phase 4 (#1009) — test if OXPHOS convergent genes show expression changes in SWI/SNF-mutant TCGA tumors
- Drug angle shifted: metformin/IACS-010759/phenformin now primary candidates (not statins)
- Code: src/cancer/swisnf_metabolic_convergence/ (01-04 scripts)
- Results: data/results/swisnf-metabolic-convergence/phase1a/, phase1b/, phase2/, phase3/
